  "prompt": "What are the top ten PC games ever?",
  "response": "Okay, compiling a definitive \"top ten\" list of PC games is incredibly subjective and depends on your criteria (influence, innovation, sales, critical acclaim, personal preference, etc.). However, based on a combination of these factors, here's a list of ten PC games that are consistently mentioned as being among the greatest and most influential:\n\n1.  **Minecraft (2011):**  A sandbox game of seemingly endless possibilities.  Its impact on creativity, modding, and gaming culture is undeniable.  It's still hugely popular and constantly evolving.\n\n2.  **Grand Theft Auto V (2015):** A crime drama story mixed with an expansive and highly detailed open world. Its online component also continues to maintain a large player base.\n\n3.  **Half-Life 2 (2004):**  A masterclass in environmental storytelling, physics-based gameplay, and immersive atmosphere.  It raised the bar for first-person shooters and remains influential in game design.\n\n4.  **The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim (2011):** A vast open-world RPG with a captivating world, compelling quests, and incredible modding community.  Its longevity and replayability are unmatched.\n\n5.  **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt (2015):** Widely praised for its rich narrative, complex characters, and stunning open world.  It's considered a benchmark for story-driven RPGs.\n\n6.  **Doom (1993):** Arguably, this defined the FPS genre and popularized network multiplayer gaming. A true game changing experience.\n\n7.  **StarCraft (1998):** A real-time strategy game so well balanced that it was the benchmark for all others that followed. \n\n8.  **Portal 2 (2011):** Ingenious puzzle design, clever writing, and memorable characters made Portal 2 a critical darling and a hugely enjoyable experience.\n\n9.  **Civilization IV (2005):** Just one in a long series, but its improvements in mechanics and visuals earned it a spot on this list.\n\n10. **Diablo II (2000):** A true classic and the grandfather of modern loot games.\n\nImportant Considerations:\n\n*   **Genre Bias:** This list inevitably leans towards certain genres.\n*   **Personal Preference:** Everyone has their favorites!\n*   **Release Date Bias:** Newer games often benefit from technological advancements and design lessons learned from older titles.\n\nThis list is a good starting point for exploring some of the most significant and acclaimed PC games ever created. Happy gaming!\n",
